1.2 Plots

Here is a basic plot done with matplotlib. It shows well nothing specific.
To visualize a plot with matplotlib in notebook you need to start a chunk of code with %Matplotlib inline, just dont ask me why ! We will cover plots later (much later) so no just copy-paste this chunk

%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

y = list(range(1,20,2))

plt.plot(x,y)
plt.ylabel('Some numbers')
plt.xlabel('Other numbers')
plt.show()

1.5 Equation

Yor final task is to write down pdf for the normal distribution, it usually terrifies my students, but you are mathematicians, so it should be a piece of cake. You only need to know how to write a fraction (\frac), square root (\sqrt)

\[\begin{equation} \label{eq:1} f(x) = \frac{1}{\sigma\sqrt{2\pi}} * e^{-\frac{1}{2}(\frac{x - \mu}{\sigma})} \end{equation}\]
